 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Ancagalon</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> There was a game I was quite excited about called Horizons, which, last I heard turned into just another offering to the Vapor Ware gods. The premise was solid, and some of the mechanics had some very fresh thinking (or seemed to). It was looking like they might have even gotten a pretty decent PVP element to boot. </P><P>The thing that kind of excited me the most was the way they were planning on developing characters. You character ages (I think whether you are online or not), the older, the more powerful. To suppliment the aging, you build skills. Seemed that this mechanic would prevent some of the gap between power-gamers and casual players. Casual gammers would only have the time to specialize and practice in a few key skills, where power-gamers would be able to add more depth to their characters by adding more skills. However, both were held in check by the chronological age of their characters. </P><P>The only thing that seemed dissapointing was the idea of item decay. The entire theory of item decay makes sense from a role-playing standpoint, but in practice is little more then a never-ending source of frustration. </P><P>For a practicle example of item decay, we can paint a picture using EQ. Stalking Probes are like Holgresh Elder Beads with item decay installed. Pretty much everyone agrees that the ability they grant is powerful, but very, very few necros bother to spend the time to keep a continuous stock. Imagine if all your items were that way. Too much work.</P><P>SWG? It is Verant. I like playing EQ. I like playing my necro. I like the friends I have made along the way. But, through it all, I think the employees at Verant are a collective bunch of ass clowns that somehow managed to fall ass-backwards into creating successful game. Their continued lack of customer service, their continued fumbling with development, their continuing lack of logical thought leave me with little hope that SWG is going to be any different. How often can Verant promise something and not deliver and still expect that we pay their salaries? EQ is the very last product I will ever purchase from Verant. Period.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> </font></td>
