        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I think DAoC was sooo close, but they dropped the ball on several things.</P><P>1.Incomplete content- This was probably one of my biggest beefs.  At the time I quit(4 months after release), there was only 1 dungeon in each realm that was itemized.  The rest of the places was nothing but coin drop.  Later on,(from what I read) when dragons and "epic battles" were introduced, you know what the loot was? NOTHING.  Dragon was dropped and not a damn thing was on him.  Can you imagine dropping Vox or Nagafen and to loot his corpse and find he had nothing on him.  Talk about a kick in the balls.</P><P>2.Class balancing- I played a kobold shadowblade.  Talk about an unfinished class.  We were promised spells, but never received them.  Hell we even had a damn mana bar, but nothing to do with it.  Stealth was horribly broken ie. pets saw through it, points into stealth had no bearing on stealth detection(was all about lvls), poisons were a joke(believe me, I put a ton of points into this skill).  Archers could do equal or greater amounts of damage from a distance than we could at melee range.  We were a kamikaze class.  Get in, one shot a caster, then die to the gang rape.  Fun..lemme tell ya.  Once they made it to where casters could not be one shotted, I left.  Got tired of all the empty promises.</P><P>3.Item upkeep- This was a pain in the ass.  "Epics" were attained every 5 lvls starting at lvl 15(?).  These items would "wear out" and have to be repaired.  Just spent 100gold on a weapon?  Guess what?  You had to pay a butt load to repair it.  Yeah, that makes sense.</P><P>4.Character advancement- Sure when you died, you respawned with all your gear and could find the place where you died, pray at your grave, and you would get some experience back.  But damn, the exp loss made EQ's look like a picnic.  Lvl'ing to higher lvls was incredibly tiresome.  If you didn't have 6 to 8 hours a day to just sit down and grind, you were screwed.  And solo'ing was a chore.</P><P>If Wow is anything BUT these problems I listed above, I'll be happy. </P><P>I will try it out just to see.  I'm curious like that <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>And personally, I love their graphics.  It's a refreshing change from the other games(UO,EQ,DAoC,etc.)</P><P>Antonin Banderas<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=290671" target="_blank">My stuff</a><BR>"No rest for the wicked"</font></td>
